summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling previous resolutions 1267 (1999), 1333 (2000), and 1363 (2001), 
Reaffirming resolutions on Afghanistan, particularly 1378 (2001) and 1383 (2001), 
Condemning terrorist attacks, including 11 September 2001, and expressing determination to prevent such acts,
Noting continued activities of Usama bin Laden and Al-Qaida,
Determining Taliban's failure to respond to demands,
Condemning Taliban for allowing terrorism and Al-Qaida for terrorist acts,
Acting under Chapter VII of the Charter,
1. Decides to continue measures imposed by resolution 1333 (2000) and terminate measures imposed in paragraph 4 (a) of resolution 1267 (1999);
2. Decides all States shall:
(a) Freeze funds, financial assets, or economic resources of Usama bin Laden, Al-Qaida, Taliban, and associated individuals, groups, undertakings, and entities;
(b) Prevent entry or transit of these individuals, except for judicial processes or Committee-approved cases;
(c) Prevent supply, sale, and transfer of arms and related materiel to these individuals, groups, undertakings, and entities;
3. Decides to review measures in 12 months;
4. Recalls obligation to implement resolution 1373 (2001) regarding Taliban, Al-Qaida, and associated individuals and entities;
5. Requests the Committee to undertake tasks and report to the Council.
The Security Council:

Establishes a Committee to:
(a) update regularly the list of individuals/entities subject to measures;
(b) seek information from States on implementation of measures;
(c) make periodic reports to the Council;
(d) promulgate guidelines/criteria for implementation;
(e) make relevant information publicly available;
(f) cooperate with other Sanctions Committees;

6. Requests States to report on steps taken to implement measures within 90 days;
7. Urges cooperation with the Committee and Monitoring Group;
8. Urges States to enforce/strengthen measures under domestic laws/regulations;

9. Requests Secretary-General to assign Monitoring Group to monitor implementation for 12 months;
10. Requests Monitoring Group to report to Committee by 31 March 2002 and every 4 months;
11. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
